      • create

        public SyncFailureHandler create(org.forgerock.json.fluent.JsonValue config)
                          throws Exception
        Create a SyncFailureHandler from the config. The config should optionally describe
        • number of retries
        • what to do upon retry exhaustion:
          • whether to save the failed sync item to a dead-letter queue
          • whether to log and ignore the failure
          • whether to call an external, user-supplied script
        Specified by:
        create in interface SyncFailureHandlerFactory
        Parameters:
        config - the config for the SyncFailureHandler
        Returns:
        the SyncFailureHandler
        Throws:
        Exception
